postcontent: I have a brand new in the Box Benchmade Bedlam AXS 8600 Automatic 1st production #31 of 500. These rare 1st production automatics are prized. These appreciate in value especially the Bedlams Auto's 1st production numbered under fifty. I paid $799.00 at a knife show from a retired Benchmade employee. The Bedlam 860 Knife initially was only made in automatic which was Awesome but! Some states consider large automatics knives illegal without a military or police exception only if carried. Benchmade noticed this, and soon came up with a lesser expensive non-automatic smaller bedlam called "The Non-Auto 8600 bedlam". The Original Benchmade 860 Bedlam Automatic design was originally designed for the Prince of Jordan’s royal guard. This is the same knife I have making it rare. Benchmade won't ever again make AXS 1st production Bedlam's Automatic like this again. Unfortunately my plans were to keep it and pass it down later in life but I am forced to sell it.
